Traceback (most recent call last):                                                     | 0/140 [00:00<?, ?it/s]\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/trainer/GenericTrainer.py\", line 241, in __sample_loop00,  2.39it/s]\r\n    self.model_sampler.sample(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/modelSampler/StableDiffusionXLSampler.py\", line 462, in sample\r\n    image = self.__sample_base(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py\", line 115, in decorate_context\r\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/modelSampler/StableDiffusionXLSampler.py\", line 167, in __sample_base\r\n    latent_image = noise_scheduler.step(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/src/diffusers/src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_euler_discrete.py\", line 586, in step\r\n    dt = self.sigmas[self.step_index + 1] - sigma_hat\r\nIndexError: index 31 is out of bounds for dimension 0 with size 31\r\nError during sampling, proceeding without sampling\r\nsampling:  96%|\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u258d  | 24/25 [00:10<00:00,  2.31it/s]\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/trainer/GenericTrainer.py\", line 241, in __sample_loop00,  2.39it/s]\r\n    self.model_sampler.sample(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/modelSampler/StableDiffusionXLSampler.py\", line 462, in sample\r\n    image = self.__sample_base(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py\", line 115, in decorate_context\r\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/modelSampler/StableDiffusionXLSampler.py\", line 167, in __sample_base\r\n    latent_image = noise_scheduler.step(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/src/diffusers/src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_dpmsolver_multistep.py\", line 991, in step\r\n    prev_sample = self.multistep_dpm_solver_second_order_update(self.model_outputs, sample=sample, noise=noise)\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/src/diffusers/src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_dpmsolver_multistep.py\", line 724, in multistep_dpm_solver_second_order_update\r\n    self.sigmas[self.step_index + 1],\r\nIndexError: index 25 is out of bounds for dimension 0 with size 25\r\nError during sampling, proceeding without sampling\r\nsampling:  97%|\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2588\u2589  | 30/31 [00:12<00:00,  2.35it/s]\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/trainer/GenericTrainer.py\", line 241, in __sample_loop00,  2.41it/s]\r\n    self.model_sampler.sample(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/modelSampler/StableDiffusionXLSampler.py\", line 462, in sample\r\n    image = self.__sample_base(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py\", line 115, in decorate_context\r\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/modules/modelSampler/StableDiffusionXLSampler.py\", line 167, in __sample_base\r\n    latent_image = noise_scheduler.step(\r\n  File \"/home/morbo/git/OneTrainer/venv/src/diffusers/src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_euler_discrete.py\", line 586, in step\r\n    dt = self.sigmas[self.step_index + 1] - sigma_hat\r\nIndexError: index 31 is out of bounds for dimension 0 with size 31\r\nError during sampling, proceeding without sampling\r\n```\n```\n\n\n### Output of `pip freeze`\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "This is a bug specific to \"Rescale Noise Schedule\" (v_prediction).\nThis is known bug but niche bug. Nerograr never got around to fixing it because he believed it only affected like one person.\n>he believed it only affected like one person.\n\nIt has a bunch of dupes, so this is unlikely :)\n> > he believed it only affected like one person.\n> \n> It has a bunch of dupes, so this is unlikely :)\n\nThis statement was made back in November 2024, was true at the time and is not unlikely. No one was training v_preds and the only reason they are now is because of NoobAI (which is a vpred finetune of Illustrious)\n\n:)\nHello, has this problem been solved? If I want to train the noobai v-pred version of lora or full fine-tuning, should I turn on Rescale Noise Schedule or \"force_v_prediction\": true in the cfg file? Can I train normally?\nonly working with DDIM sampler, all others fail in my experience\n\nwould be great if this could be fixed, DDIM is not particularly great\nWhen will it be repaired\n> This is a bug specific to \"Rescale Noise Schedule\" (v_prediction).\n\nI tested it with rescale noise schedule set to false, and was still getting the error.\nSo probably its related to force v-prediction instead?\nMet this bug yesterday. The same error if \"Rescale noise Scheduler\" is enabled\nsame error without ddim sampler... \nSeems like there are two separate issues. One affecting DDPM and one affecting rest of samplers.\n\nSamplers other than DDPM and DDIM work after simple check in `force_last_timestep`  if last timestep isn't already here (probably they are adding them internally. I didn't checked) and not adding duplicate.\n\nDDPM still crashes after this change, but I'm still checking cause.\n\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "This is a bug specific to \"Rescale Noise Schedule\" (v_prediction).\nThis is known bug but niche bug. Nerograr never got around to fixing it because he believed it only affected like one person.\n>he believed it only affected like one person.\n\nIt has a bunch of dupes, so this is unlikely :)\n> > he believed it only affected like one person.\n> \n> It has a bunch of dupes, so this is unlikely :)\n\nThis statement was made back in November 2024, was true at the time and is not unlikely. No one was training v_preds and the only reason they are now is because of NoobAI (which is a vpred finetune of Illustrious)\n\n:)\nHello, has this problem been solved? If I want to train the noobai v-pred version of lora or full fine-tuning, should I turn on Rescale Noise Schedule or \"force_v_prediction\": true in the cfg file? Can I train normally?\nonly working with DDIM sampler, all others fail in my experience\n\nwould be great if this could be fixed, DDIM is not particularly great\nWhen will it be repaired\n> This is a bug specific to \"Rescale Noise Schedule\" (v_prediction).\n\nI tested it with rescale noise schedule set to false, and was still getting the error.\nSo probably its related to force v-prediction instead?\nMet this bug yesterday. The same error if \"Rescale noise Scheduler\" is enabled\nsame error without ddim sampler... \nSeems like there are two separate issues. One affecting DDPM and one affecting rest of samplers.\n\nSamplers other than DDPM and DDIM work after simple check in `force_last_timestep`  if last timestep isn't already here (probably they are adding them internally. I didn't checked) and not adding duplicate.\n\nDDPM still crashes after this change, but I'm still checking cause.\n\n\nhttps://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/pull/965 If anyone have time, you can test it.\n> [#965](https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/pull/965) If anyone have time, you can test it.\n\nCan confirm, this fixes Sampling on VPRED, thank you <3\nThis bug is now closed thanks to Heasterian's fix, thank you!\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/25a2e1b89f707709fafd544e0c94254b73729e3c", "https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/225689ef8ac280402614e74e4c95527ad112e04b", "https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/e39e1564310a4ca7c345b901f274f5b504fd61e8"], "created_at": "2025-09-01T19:18:22Z"}
{"repo": "Nerogar/OneTrainer", "pull_number": 1293, "instance_id": "Nerogar__OneTrainer-1293", "issue_numbers": [1288], "base_commit": "5405289243e3310ac03e216295383129781ac5e5", "patch": "diff --git a/modules/modelSaver/zImage/ZImageModelSaver.py b/modules/modelSaver/zImage/ZImageModelSaver.py\nindex 82b39f01b..1d8f85495 100644\n--- a/modules/modelSaver/zImage/ZImageModelSaver.py\n+++ b/modules/modelSaver/zImage/ZImageModelSaver.py\n@@ -58,6 +58,8 @@ def __save_safetensors(\n \n         os.makedirs(Path(destination).parent.absolute(), exist_ok=True)\n \n+        print(\"Warning: Comfy can only load their own incompatible format of Z-Image full finetunes. To use this file in Comfy, it can be converted using https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/z_image_turbo/resolve/main/z_image_convert_original_to_comfy.py\")\n+\n         save_file(save_state_dict, destination, self._create_safetensors_header(model, save_state_dict))\n \n     def __save_internal(\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Z-Image Fine-Tune only noise in ComfyUI\n\n### Discussed in https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/discussions/1287\n\n- [x] Wait for https://github.com/Comfy-Org/ComfyUI/issues/12303\n- [x] If they don't change it, add a warning to OneTrainer that informs the user of the convert script\n- [x] Otherwise, implement conversion to the original keys in OneTrainer\n\n\n", "hints_text": "the incompatible format is intentional by Comfy: https://github.com/Comfy-Org/ComfyUI/issues/12303#issuecomment-3856430923\n\n", "all_hints_text": "the incompatible format is intentional by Comfy: https://github.com/Comfy-Org/ComfyUI/issues/12303#issuecomment-3856430923\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/fe6c4af95fb3719759a7632d60865101d6397b67"], "created_at": "2026-02-06T10:11:19Z"}
{"repo": "Nerogar/OneTrainer", "pull_number": 1305, "instance_id": "Nerogar__OneTrainer-1305", "issue_numbers": [1304], "base_commit": "9a270603a10b7a354b36ccb9d94ba7e2575c821d", "patch": "diff --git a/requirements-global.txt b/requirements-global.txt\nindex 26a4b4cec..70fb19159 100644\n--- a/requirements-global.txt\n+++ b/requirements-global.txt\n@@ -12,6 +12,7 @@ av==16.1.0\n yt-dlp  #no pinned version, frequently updated for compatibility with sites\n scenedetect==0.6.6\n parse==1.20.2\n+setuptools==81.0.0\n \n # pytorch\n accelerate==1.7.0\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Modern versions of setuptools no longer bundle pkg_resources\n### What happened?\n\nWhenever attempting to start TensorBoard on the latest OneTrainer in environments where the `setuptools` version >=82.0.0, TensorBoard fails with the error `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'pkg_resources'`.\n\n### What did you expect would happen?\n\nI expected that TensorBoard would run properly without throwing any errors.\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/home/redacted/onetrainer-old/OneTrainer/venv/bin/tensorboard\", line 3, in <module>\n    from tensorboard.main import run_main\n  File \"/home/redacted/onetrainer-old/OneTrainer/venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/tensorboard/main.py\", line 27, in <module>\n    from tensorboard import default\n  File \"/home/redacted/onetrainer-old/OneTrainer/venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/tensorboard/default.py\", line 30, in <module>\n    import pkg_resources\nModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'pkg_resources'\n```\n\n### Generate and upload debug_report.log\n\n[debug_report.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/25219195/debug_report.log)\n", "hints_text": "As a temporary workaround, you can run `pip3 install setuptools==81.0` in your `venv` environment, which will downgrade `setuptools` to the latest version that still supports OneTrainer's software stack ([source](https://setuptools.pypa.io/en/stable/history.html#v82-0-0)).\n\n", "all_hints_text": "As a temporary workaround, you can run `pip3 install setuptools==81.0` in your `venv` environment, which will downgrade `setuptools` to the latest version that still supports OneTrainer's software stack ([source](https://setuptools.pypa.io/en/stable/history.html#v82-0-0)).\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/e100369e6efcbfb1e3c2fe58738000270a5dd86a", "https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/ca04d16d4bcff05f2bd69d92d24c86949b4a21bc", "https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/723b8a6e6fad7189a2dabd74d5637d4cb392eebd"], "created_at": "2026-02-10T20:04:49Z"}
{"repo": "Nerogar/OneTrainer", "pull_number": 1297, "instance_id": "Nerogar__OneTrainer-1297", "issue_numbers": [1311], "base_commit": "d8915b47e420826ac4dc9146c8733561e36519b2", "patch": "diff --git a/modules/modelLoader/BaseModelLoader.py b/modules/modelLoader/BaseModelLoader.py\nindex 138eda4cd..4a560c2f1 100644\n--- a/modules/modelLoader/BaseModelLoader.py\n+++ b/modules/modelLoader/BaseModelLoader.py\n@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@\n from abc import ABCMeta, abstractmethod\n \n from modules.model.BaseModel import BaseModel\n+from modules.util.config.TrainConfig import QuantizationConfig\n from modules.util.enum.ModelType import ModelType\n from modules.util.ModelNames import ModelNames\n from modules.util.ModelWeightDtypes import ModelWeightDtypes\n@@ -47,5 +48,6 @@ def load(\n             model_type: ModelType,\n             model_names: ModelNames,\n             weight_dtypes: ModelWeightDtypes,\n+            quantization: QuantizationConfig,\n     ) -> BaseModel | None:\n         pass\ndiff --git a/modules/modelSaver/GenericLoRAModelSaver.py b/modules/modelSaver/GenericLoRAModelSaver.py\nindex 59955dc8b..3b4ad2c2b 100644\n--- a/modules/modelSaver/GenericLoRAModelSaver.py\n+++ b/modules/modelSaver/GenericLoRAModelSaver.py\n@@ -38,7 +38,9 @@ def save(\n \n             if embedding_saver_class is not None:\n                 embedding_model_saver = embedding_saver_class()\n-                if not model.train_config.bundle_additional_embeddings or output_model_format == ModelFormat.INTERNAL:\n+                if ((model.train_config is not None and not model.train_config.bundle_additional_embeddings) \\\n+                    or output_model_format == ModelFormat.INTERNAL\n+                ):\n                     embedding_model_saver.save_multiple(model, output_model_format, output_model_destination, dtype)\n \n             if output_model_format == ModelFormat.INTERNAL:\ndiff --git a/modules/ui/ConvertModelUI.py b/modules/ui/ConvertModelUI.py\nindex 837b27614..db4de37e1 100644\n--- a/modules/ui/ConvertModelUI.py\n+++ b/modules/ui/ConvertModelUI.py\n@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@\n \n from modules.util import create\n from modules.util.args.ConvertModelArgs import ConvertModelArgs\n+from modules.util.config.TrainConfig import QuantizationConfig\n from modules.util.enum.DataType import DataType\n from modules.util.enum.ModelFormat import ModelFormat\n from modules.util.enum.ModelType import ModelType\n@@ -65,9 +66,11 @@ def main_frame(self, master):\n             (\"PixArt Sigma\", ModelType.PIXART_SIGMA),\n             (\"Flux Dev\", ModelType.FLUX_DEV_1),\n             (\"Flux Fill Dev\", ModelType.FLUX_FILL_DEV_1),\n+            (\"Flux 2\", ModelType.FLUX_2),\n             (\"Hunyuan Video\", ModelType.HUNYUAN_VIDEO),\n             (\"Chroma1\", ModelType.CHROMA_1), #TODO does this just work? HiDream is not here\n             (\"QwenImage\", ModelType.QWEN), #TODO does this just work? HiDream is not here\n+            (\"ZImage\", ModelType.Z_IMAGE),\n         ], self.ui_state, \"model_type\")\n \n         # training method\n@@ -131,17 +134,18 @@ def convert_model(self):\n                         base_model=self.convert_model_args.input_name,\n                     ),\n                     weight_dtypes=self.convert_model_args.weight_dtypes(),\n-                    #TODO quantization layer filter\n+                    quantization=QuantizationConfig.default_values(),\n                 )\n             elif self.convert_model_args.training_method in [TrainingMethod.LORA, TrainingMethod.EMBEDDING]:\n                 model = model_loader.load(\n                     model_type=self.convert_model_args.model_type,\n                     model_names=ModelNames(\n+                        base_model=None,\n                         lora=self.convert_model_args.input_name,\n                         embedding=EmbeddingName(str(uuid4()), self.convert_model_args.input_name),\n                     ),\n                     weight_dtypes=self.convert_model_args.weight_dtypes(),\n-                    #TODO quantization layer filter\n+                    quantization=QuantizationConfig.default_values(),\n                 )\n             else:\n                 raise Exception(\"could not load model: \" + self.convert_model_args.input_name)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Convert Model Tools - throws missing 1 required positional argument: 'quantization'\n### What happened?\n\nI ran convert_model.py to convert a backup lora into a full lora.  I wasn't sure if I was passing all the same parameters correctly so then tried it under the UI.  Noticed Z-Image wasn't there so I added it to components.options_kv as follows:\n(\"Z-Image\", ModelType.Z_IMAGE),\n\nIt ran and gave the same error.  Here is the error I see\n\nStarting UI...\nLoading model D:/zimage-workspace/save/backup/2026-02-10_15-56-24-backup-8954-37-0/lora/lora.safetensors\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"C:\\src\\OneTrainer\\modules\\ui\\ConvertModelUI.py\", line 138, in convert_model\n    model = model_loader.load(\n            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: make_lora_model_loader.<locals>.GenericLoRAModelLoader.load() missing 1 required positional argument: 'quantization'\n\nSo there are two issues here, the first is the missing parameter 'quantization'\n\nThe other is the UI for this tool also needs updated to handle newer models.\n\nI tried tracing through this and it was a bit too complicated for me to figure out, but it looks like more than quantization is needed.  I tried setting the values to default in GenericLoRAModelLoader to get past this, but it also needs base_model to be passed which I couldn't figure out how to set it.\n\n### What did you expect would happen?\n\nI expected it to convert, instead it error.\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\nLoading model D:/zimage-workspace/save/backup/2026-02-10_15-56-24-backup-8954-37-0/lora/lora.safetensors\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"C:\\src\\OneTrainer\\modules\\ui\\ConvertModelUI.py\", line 138, in convert_model\n    model = model_loader.load(\n            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: make_lora_model_loader.<locals>.GenericLoRAModelLoader.load() missing 1 required positional argument: 'quantization'\n```\n\n### Generate and upload debug_report.log\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "fixed in https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/pull/1297\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/184bce7b8648ee9931a25d94fe022e28179206dd", "https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/65b7f9fb03d33038e2e18b1516675da14280a69e", "https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/cc6fa342ba961ed82eac3036a270884d9f5315a4"], "created_at": "2026-02-07T20:12:32Z"}
{"repo": "Nerogar/OneTrainer", "pull_number": 1426, "instance_id": "Nerogar__OneTrainer-1426", "issue_numbers": [1390], "base_commit": "b734d60f2d334f18da188a0a96eeb8e0e75b5208", "patch": "diff --git a/scripts/generate_debug_report.py b/scripts/generate_debug_report.py\nindex b6b6e69bd..29b7147b2 100644\n--- a/scripts/generate_debug_report.py\n+++ b/scripts/generate_debug_report.py\n@@ -879,48 +879,69 @@ class NetworkInfo:\n     @staticmethod\n     def test_url(url: str) -> str:\n         \"\"\"\n-        Test network connectivity by pinging the host extracted from a URL.\n-        Reports packet loss from the ping command.\n+        Test network connectivity using both HTTPS and ping.\n         \"\"\"\n-        logger.info(f\"Pinging URL: {url}\")\n+        logger.info(f\"Testing URL: {url}\")\n+\n         parsed = urlparse(url)\n-        host = parsed.netloc\n-        count = \"4\"  # Number of ping packets\n+        host = parsed.netloc or parsed.path\n+\n+        if not host:\n+            return f\"Failure: could not parse host from URL: {url}\"\n+\n+        https_status = NetworkInfo._test_https(url, host)\n+        ping_status = NetworkInfo._test_ping(host)\n+\n+        return f\"{https_status}; {ping_status}\"\n+\n+    @staticmethod\n+    def _test_https(url: str, host: str) -> str:\n+        try:\n+            response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n+\n+            if 200 <= response.status_code < 400:\n+                return f\"HTTPS to {host} succeeded: Status code {response.status_code}\"\n+\n+            return f\"HTTPS to {host} returned status code {response.status_code}\"\n+\n+        except requests.exceptions.Timeout:\n+            return f\"HTTPS to {host} failed: timed out\"\n+        except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError as e:\n+            return f\"HTTPS to {host} failed: connection error: {e}\"\n+        except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n+            return f\"HTTPS to {host} failed: {e}\"\n+\n+    @staticmethod\n+    def _test_ping(host: str) -> str:\n+        count = \"5\"\n \n         cmd = (\n             [\"ping\", \"-n\", count, host]\n             if platform.system() == \"Windows\"\n             else [\"ping\", \"-c\", count, host]\n         )\n+\n         try:\n             result = Utility.subprocess_run(cmd)\n-            output = result.stdout\n+            output = result.stdout or \"\"\n+\n             packet_loss = \"Unavailable\"\n+\n             if platform.system() == \"Windows\":\n-                m = re.search(r\"\\((\\d+)% loss\\)\", output)\n-                if m:\n-                    packet_loss = f\"{m.group(1)}%\"\n+                match = re.search(r\"\\((\\d+)% loss\\)\", output)\n             else:\n-                m = re.search(r\"(\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?)% packet loss\", output)\n-                if m:\n-                    packet_loss = f\"{m.group(1)}%\"\n-            return f\"Ping to {host} successful: Packet Loss: {packet_loss}\"\n+                match = re.search(r\"(\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?)% packet loss\", output)\n+\n+            if match:\n+                packet_loss = f\"{match.group(1)}%\"\n+\n+            return f\"Ping to {host} succeeded: Packet loss {packet_loss}\"\n+\n         except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n-            logger.warning(\n-                f\"Ping to {host} failed. Using requests fallback. Error: {e}\"\n-            )\n-            try:\n-                r = requests.get(url, timeout=5)\n-                if r.status_code == 200:\n-                    return f\"Requests to {host} succeeded (fallback).\"\n-                else:\n-                    return f\"Requests to {host} failed (fallback). Status code: {r.status_code}\"\n-            except Exception as ex:\n-                logger.exception(\"Requests fallback failed\")\n-                return f\"Requests fallback also failed: {ex}\"\n+            stderr = e.stderr or \"\"\n+            return f\"Ping to {host} failed: {stderr.strip() or 'command failed'}\"\n         except Exception as e:\n-            logger.exception(\"Unexpected error during ping\")\n-            return f\"Failure: {e}\"\n+            return f\"Ping to {host} failed: {e}\"\n \n     @staticmethod\n     def test_connectivity() -> dict[str, tuple[str, str]]:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Debug script error messages / NoneType\n### What happened?\n\ntken from https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/issues/1389 at the bottom, the debug script created this:\n\n```\nPyPI (https://pypi.org/): Failure: expected string or bytes-like object, got 'NoneType'\nHuggingFace (https://huggingface.co/): Failure: expected string or bytes-like object, got 'NoneType'\nGoogle (https://www.google.com/): Failure: expected string or bytes-like object, got 'NoneType'\n```\n@O-J1 \n\n### What did you expect would happen?\n\nsee above\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Generate and upload debug_report.log\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Nerogar/OneTrainer/commit/fecd6b1d837efa096be3e56b22fff5c4d1e9caa1"], "created_at": "2026-04-26T09:08:37Z"}
